Monroe Street, north side, east from a point slightly east of Scammel Street, showing several tenement units separated by previous demolitions. These are shortly to follow as shown in View 2. Upon this site will rise the government sponsored public housing project, Vladeck Houses. The two four story buildings in the foreground of the earlier photo, bear No's. 237-39.

Monroe Street, west across Scammel Street, showing the westerly portion of the demolition for the government sponsored public housing project, Vladeck Houses. At the left, behind the tenements at the S.E. corner of Scammel Street, appears the Public School (No. 31) at Gouverneur Street. This will remain. View 2 is slightly westward, showing Scammel Street in the foreground. The block frontage between this and Gouverneur Street has been cleared.

Monroe Street, north side, between Scammel and Jackson Street's, showing the northeasterly portion of the site for the USHA "Vladeck Houses" being cleared. This is on this side of Jackson Street, towards which the photographer is viewing. Madison Street is opened to view on the left. Public School No. 12 is at the N.W. corner of these two thoroughfares and will remain.
